      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLACK WANDA (7) produced a moderate run last time when fifth at Angle Park over 342m behind Conner's Rain (20.35) in a TG1-4W. Has good speed and can quickly clear the pack out wide. Can make amends. BOUNDING HOME (8) has gone well at his last couple of runs here, most recently when third beaten 4.5 lengths (23.21). Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Can measure up. SEBON KNIGHT (5) finds it hard to win. Finished in the money last time though when third (23.26) at this track. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Expecting another good run. CREEPER (4) saluted last start after racing on the speed. Sure to run well again.",
